  "title": "La Rochefoucauld §laroch_087: Men would not live long in society were they not the dupes of each other.",
  "body": "Men would not live long in society were they not the dupes of each other. [A maxim, adds Aime Martin, \"Which may enter into the code of a vulgar rogue, but one is astonished to find it in a moral treatise.\" Yet we have scriptural authority for it: \"Deceiving and being deceived.\"--2 TIM. iii. 13.]",
